events.name: Social Coding
events.description: A space for women coders to learn from each other, to practice and discuss learnings with fellow peers. This would be a monthly event of informal space to do coding on open source projects. So bring your pet projects along or join one of our existing teams/ projects to work on. Featured Projects:https://trello.com/b/kl2BTwil/wwc-sg-social-coding-projects First timers, please read:Newbies Step-by-step Guide (https://www.meetup.com/Women-Who-Code-Singapore/pages/22271496/Social_Coding_Guide/) Please bring your own laptop. Refreshments will be provided. Agenda:6:30p - Start coding! ^_^8:30p - End session Psst, this event is intended for ladies only. All attendees kindly read and abide by the Women Who Code Code of Conduct - https://github.com/WomenWhoCode/guidelines-resources/blob/master/code_of_conduct.md

events.name: The Impact of Artificial Intelligence on Achieving the SDGs
events.description: Please register here, https://www.sginnovate.com/events/impact-artificial-intelligence-achieving-sdgs The Impact of Artificial Intelligence on Achieving the SDGs Presented by General Assembly and SGInnovate The Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs), otherwise known as the Global Goals, are a universal call to action to end poverty, protect the planet and ensure that all people enjoy peace and prosperity. Join us for this event and learn from the panel of experts how artificial intelligence can help to solve global challenges.
